    "intro": "NeuroForge is a cross-platform app for running neural networks locally.",
    "sections": {
      "system": "System: manage RAM, CPU cores, GPU, and process priorities.",
      "network": "Network: three isolation modes. In API-only mode, the AI can only reach whitelisted endpoints (e.g. Hugging Face). All requests are visible in the network monitor.",
      "memory": "Memory: STM holds recent chat context. LTM stores long-term facts with semantic search. Memory can be transferred between chats and models.",
      "injection": "Global injections: unique feature — text added to every message (prefix, suffix, hidden context, memory summary).",
      "agents": "Agents: combine neural networks into groups with roles (coordinator, researcher, executor). Each agent has its own internet, device, and memory permissions.",
